-- China, Japan Support President Sarkozy's G20 Agenda, French Official Says
-- B y   H e l e n e   F o u q u e t
-- 2010-10-04T19:04:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-04/china-japan-support-president-sarkozy-s-g20-agenda-french-official-says.html
China and Japan support French
President Nicolas Sarkozy’s agenda on currencies and commodities
ahead of his presidency of the Group of 20 nations after a
meeting in Seoul next month, a French official said today.  Chinese Premier Hu Jintao will visit France ahead of the
meeting in Seoul on Nov. 12, the official, who cannot be named
according to French government rules, told reporters in
Brussels, where Sarkozy met Asian leaders at a Europe-Asia
summit. France takes over from Korea at the helm of the G20 in
November.   Hu Jintao said at the summit that France and China will
sign an accord on the French G20 presidency agenda during his
visit to France, according to the French official.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Helene Fouquet in Paris at 
 hfouquet1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
